						               													<description>It is said that angels poured courage into a seed, then planted it into the soil of the human world, and that is how sunflowers came to be.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;And so it happens that on a beautiful island a student-led social movement breaks out. If only they can find the legendary sunflower that hides great power within him, the movement can prevail, and so the student leader will use any means necessary to find it; but the government is dispatching police to hinder him, spread disinformation and sow confusion. What kind of future will the island have?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Who is the Sunflower is a microgame in which two secret teams face off, trying to discover each other's identity. Each player gets an identity card. Some characters need to identify certain other character (e.g. Student wants to find Sunflower), while others need to be identified by certain character (Banana wants to be found by the Student). After some discussion, players that need to find another character can attempt to guess who that character is. If this fulfills any player's victory condition, the round ends, with those players scoring a point each.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
